question: What is the submission process for research papers?
answer: IEEE ICDE 2023 will have three rounds of research paper submissions with each round involving two rounds of reviewing to allow for revisions. Notification dates are approximate. All deadlines are 11:59PM PST. The first round submission is due on April 25th 2022 (Monday), the second round submission is due on July 8th 2022 (Friday), and the third round submission is due on October 8th 2022 (Saturday).The submission website is https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/ICDE2023. The site will be open for submissions at least two weeks before the deadline.

question: Do we have to submit an abstract before the manuscript deadline?
answer: No, you do not have to submit an abstract before the manuscript deadline.

question: Are there any tutorials related to graph neural network(GNN) in this conference? If so, what are their title and organizers?
answer: Yes, there are one tutorial related to graph neural network in this conference. The title of the tutorial is “Graph Neural Networks for Tabular Data Learning” and the organizers are Cheng-Te Li, Yu-Che Tsai, Jay Chiehen Liao.
